        "content": "# Fix Eval tab: show live DB results + metric counters instead of stale JSON file\n\nYour orchestrator is cec50b17:0. Work inside `.synapse/worktrees/developer-25-eval-tab-live`. Commit your changes. Do not push.\n\n## The problem\n\nThe Eval tab currently reads from `tests/eval_report.json` (a stale static file from the last manual run). Phase 1 built a live `eval_results` DB table that auto-populates after every completed task. The Eval tab should show that live data instead.\n\n## Changes needed\n\n### Change 1 — New dashboard endpoint (src/dashboard.ts)\n\nAdd `GET /api/eval/live` that returns all eval results from the DB, joined with task titles, sorted newest first:\n\n```typescript\napp.get('/api/eval/live', (_req: Request, res: Response) => {\n  const { getAllEvalResults } = require('./db.js'); // or import\n  res.json(getAllEvalResults());\n});\n```\n\nAdd `getAllEvalResults()` to `src/db.ts`:\n```typescript\nexport function getAllEvalResults(): {\n  task_id: number; title: string; agent_id: string;\n  metrics: { metric: string; passed: boolean; value: number | null }[];\n  pass: boolean; created_at: number;\n}[]\n```\n\nQuery:\n```sql\nSELECT t.id as task_id, t.title, t.agent_id,\n       er.metric, er.passed, er.value, er.created_at\nFROM eval_results er\nJOIN tasks t ON t.id = er.task_id\nORDER BY er.created_at DESC\n```\n\nGroup by task_id in TypeScript (not SQL) — collect metrics per task, compute `pass = all metrics passed`.\n\nAlso add `GET /api/eval/counts` if not already present (it was added in Phase 1 — verify it exists in dashboard.ts).\n\n### Change 2 — Frontend (public/app.js)\n\nReplace the `fetch('/api/eval/report')` call in `renderEval()` with `fetch('/api/eval/live')`. The response format is different — adapt the rendering:\n\nEach item has: `{ task_id, title, agent_id, metrics: [{metric, passed, value}], pass, created_at }`\n\n**Replace the failed/passed rendering with:**\n\n```javascript\n// Fetch live results and metric counts\nconst [liveResults, counts] = await Promise.all([\n  fetch('/api/eval/live').then(r => r.json()),\n  fetch('/api/eval/counts').then(r => r.json()),\n  // keep proposals fetch\n]);\n\n// Metric counter summary bar (at top of eval content)\nconst METRICS = ['traceability', 'tool_calls', 'duration', 'has_commit'];\nconst THRESHOLD = 3;\nconst counterHtml = `<div class=\"eval-counters\">\n  ${METRICS.map(m => {\n    const count = counts[m] ?? 0;\n    const pct = Math.min(count / THRESHOLD, 1);\n    const color = count >= THRESHOLD ? 'var(--p0)' : count >= 2 ? 'var(--warn)' : 'var(--muted)';\n    return `<div class=\"eval-counter\">\n      <span style=\"color:${color}\">${m}: ${count}/${THRESHOLD}</span>\n    </div>`;\n  }).join('')}\n</div>`;\n\n// Task rows: newest first, show PASS or FAIL + metric chips\nconst failed = liveResults.filter(r => !r.pass);\nconst passed = liveResults.filter(r => r.pass);\n\nconst failedHtml = failed.map(r => `\n  <div class=\"eval-row eval-fail\">\n    <div class=\"eval-row-header\">\n      <span class=\"eval-id\">#${r.task_id}</span>\n      <span class=\"eval-label bad\">FAIL</span>\n      <span style=\"font-size:9px;color:var(--muted)\">${new Date(r.created_at).toLocaleTimeString([], {hour12:false})}</span>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"eval-title\">${esc(r.title.slice(0, 55))}</div>\n    <div class=\"eval-failures\">${r.metrics.filter(m => !m.passed).map(m =>\n      `<span class=\"eval-chip\">${esc(m.metric)}=${m.value ?? '✗'}</span>`\n    ).join('')}</div>\n  </div>`).join('');\n\nconst passedHtml = passed.map(r => `\n  <div class=\"eval-row eval-pass\">\n    <span class=\"eval-id\">#${r.task_id}</span>\n    <span class=\"eval-label good\">PASS</span>\n    <span class=\"eval-title-inline\">${esc(r.title.slice(0, 45))}</span>\n  </div>`).join('');\n```\n\nUpdate the `el.innerHTML` to include `counterHtml` at the top, before the Failed/Passed sections.\n\nRemove the `gateByTask` / `gate` fetch from `renderEval()` — that was for the old batch eval. Keep the `proposals` fetch.\n\nKeep the \"▶ Run improvement loop\" button (it's still useful for running a full historical rescan) but remove the gate section from the failed rows.\n\n### Change 3 — CSS (public/style.css)\n\nAdd minimal styles for `.eval-counters` and `.eval-counter` if needed (they can reuse existing classes — check what's there first).\n\nBuild with `npm run build` and verify clean.\n",
